    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Dangerous Movies?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Cody Lyon letter on Sept 14 article opposes threat of government intervention if entertainment industry does not try to curb violence</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>It is troubling to see politicians threatening the entertainment industry with government intervention if it doesn't make attempts to curb violence (front page, Sept. 14).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>It is troubling to see politicians threatening the entertainment industry with government intervention if it doesn't make attempts to curb violence (front page, Sept. 14).</p>
        <p>Perhaps these mostly middle-aged men have forgotten that in their childhood they probably enjoyed countless westerns, gangster dramas or war movies. It would be ludicrous to assume that any of these men assumed a life of crime as a result of watching the carnage depicted in those movies.</p>
        <p>One can only hope that those who threaten intrusive legislation recognize that the gratuitous violence one finds in Hollywood films is no more capable of desensitizing a child today than it was 40 years ago.</p>
        <p>CODY LYON  New York, Sept. 14, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
